snippet: The Australian Adam Hansen won the hilly 19th stage while Alberto Contador maintained the red leader’s jersey with two days to go.
abstract: Australian cyclist Adam Hansen wins 19th stage of the Vuelta a Espana, while Spain's Alberto Contador retains overall lead.
lead_paragraph: The Australian Adam Hansen won the hilly 19th stage while Alberto Contador maintained the red leader’s jersey with two days to go.

headline.main: Australian Wins Stage in Vuelta a España
